content: On one hand it's a fine game probably around 4 stars (nothing new really, just another Kairosoft game), but the monetization scheme feels sooo wrong. You pay for the game upfront, then you have premium currency (which you can get slowly, by enabling ads IN A PAID GAME) and on to of that a subscription to enable some additional features. Sure, those things are optional, but this feels very exploitative, and those practices need to stop.

Fun, cute, engaging Japanese train station sim!  This game is easily one of the most fun and addictive games I've played, and is on my 'daily play' list. Controls are intuitive. The gameplay is steady-paced enough to remain interesting for extended periods, yet also relaxed and forgiving enough to minimize frustration.  Even with the English translation, the aesthetics are spot-on for a Japanese train station, and the grapics are bright, cheerful, and well rendered.

As for the time given for how long things take to build - they are in game hours, not real time. Excellent addition to Kairo imo
